---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import { loadCatalogue } from "../../lib/catalogue";

const entries = loadCatalogue();

// Placeholder rows. These are NOT real launch windows — see banner.
// They exist only so the page layout/navigation is stable.
const placeholderRows = entries
  .filter((e) => e.bodies.includes("E") && e.bodies.includes("M"))
  .slice(0, 5)
  .map((e) => ({
    id: e.id,
    name: e.name,
    period_yr: e.period.years,
  }));
---
<Base title="Launch windows (preview)" description="Forthcoming: per-cycler launch window forecasts.">
  <h1>Launch windows</h1>

  <div class="banner">
    <strong>Preview.</strong> The data below is a layout placeholder. Real launch-window
    forecasts require the phase-matching code from
    <a href="https://github.com/Bwooce/cyclers">milestone M6 of the upstream cyclers project</a>,
    which doesn't exist yet. No real launch dates are shown — the table below contains no
    numerical windows. This page exists so navigation is stable; it will be populated when M6
    lands.
  </div>

  <p>
    Once the phase-matching pipeline produces a ledger of launch opportunities, each row in
    the table below will show the next several launch windows for that cycler: the launch
    date, the launch C₃, the V∞ at injection, and the time-of-flight to the first encounter.
    Per the design spec, windows will be tagged with the same V0–V5 validation level as the
    cycler they belong to.
  </p>

  <h2>Cyclers eligible for window forecasts</h2>
  <p class="muted">
    Earth-touching cyclers in the current catalogue ({placeholderRows.length} of {entries.length}
    entries). Real launch dates will appear here once M6 lands.
  </p>

  <table class="catalogue">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th scope="col">Cycler</th>
        <th scope="col">Period (yr)</th>
        <th scope="col">Next window</th>
        <th scope="col">C₃</th>
        <th scope="col">TOF to first encounter</th>
        <th scope="col">Validation</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {placeholderRows.map((r) => (
        <tr>
          <td><a href={`/cycler/${r.id}/`}>{r.name}</a></td>
          <td class="right">{r.period_yr.toFixed(2)}</td>
          <td class="muted">— pending M6 —</td>
          <td class="muted">—</td>
          <td class="muted">—</td>
          <td><span class="vlevel">N/A</span></td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>What "M6" means</h2>
  <p>
    Milestone M6 in the upstream <a href="https://github.com/Bwooce/cyclers">cyclers</a> spec
    is the phase-matching pipeline: given a validated cycler geometry and a real ephemeris,
    find calendar dates where Earth phases into the geometry within an injection budget. The
    outputs feed this page directly — see spec §12.1 of the upstream repo.
  </p>
</Base>
